<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1341,2017]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1776,1801]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Remarks</emphasis>
. Externally, this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Masunaga, 2017" authorityName="Masunaga" authorityYear="2017" box="[724,935,1776,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Scorpiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thorpei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[724,935,1776,1800]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Scorpiurus thorpei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[942,1031,1776,1801]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[942,1031,1776,1801]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parent" authorityYear="1932" box="[1088,1230,1777,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Scorpiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenescens">
<emphasis box="[1088,1230,1777,1800]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">S. aenescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from those of the new species in having acrostichal setae on the flat area in front of the scutellum, its femora concolorous with the pleura except for their apical parts and, in the male dorsally bent posterior abdominal segments and a ventrally directed hypopygium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1341,2017]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
Adults fly very quickly near the ground, so it is difficult to catch in the open with a net. The inlet at my main survey site near Linkwater, South Island, has wide tidal flats covered with short reeds (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1269,1956,1981]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1928,1950]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitat of the genus Scorpiurus. A, Landscape of the sampling site. Near Linkwater, South Island, New Zealand; B, Enlarged view of habitat." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/998374/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). By sweeping the reeds on which the flies were resting with a butterfly net, I was able to catch many of them.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
